It is another milestone in the more than three decades of progress in addressing one of humanity's greatest health challenges".
Deborah Gold, chief executive of NAT, said: "This is a pivotal moment in the fight against HIV.
PrEP, when targeted at people in need and at risk, offers the opportunity to change the English HIV epidemic.
From September, people at high risk for HIV will have access to this NHS-funded trial in England to develop a new tool that is really individually controlled and not subject to negotiation with a partner, which will lead to the improvement of many, many lives.
